The Senior Manager, Treasury Analytics provides analytical support to the International Treasury team to facilitate effective governance and strategy orchestration on key topics such as Interest Rate Risk management, liquidity risk management, investments and FX hedging for treasury locations across Latin America, Central America and the Caribbean locations of the bank.

ACCOUNTABILITIES
1. Work on development and implementation of balance sheet analytics related to,
Modelling non-maturity deposits;
Calibrating mortgage prepayment rate;
Modelling term deposits with early redemptions

2. Develop tools and work on ad-hoc analysis related to,
Interest Rate Risk i.e. simulation of balance sheet and interest rate movements;
Liquidity risk and metrics such as Liquidity Coverage Ratio;
Investment portfolio across IB locations;
FX hedging: recommend hedging strategies along with analytics based on market driven events;
Develop tools to analyze impact of key balance sheet changes such as asset composition, funding mix and rate movements;
Management reporting: Develop, implement and maintain weekly, monthly, quarterly and ad-hoc reports

3. Ensure alignment of ALM methodology, measurement and policies
Work closely and coordinate on topics such as balance sheet management, risk limits, key exposures, regulatory initiatives etc.;
Participate and work on regulatory initiatives such as IRRBB and FRTB while working with GRM and Treasury;
Review ALM related policies for different countries and update the International Treasury guidelines.

4. Maintain working relationships with internal stakeholders such as local Treasury teams and the relevant support functions

SKILLS, EXPERIENCES AND FUNCTIONAL COMPETENCIES REQUIRED:
Undergraduate in Business, Finance or Accounting;
CFA / FRM designations is desirable
Solid knowledge of Financial Products including money market and derivative products;
Proficiency with use of Excel, VBA, Bloomberg and programming language(s) such as Python;
Understanding of the Scotiabank operations and Finance systems (INEA);
Familiarity with the relevant regulations i.e. IRRBB, FRTB, Basel 3, Volcker;
Exceptional communication skills, both verbal and written;
Self-driven, analytical and colloborative;
Ability to speak Spanish
Location(s): Canada : Ontario : Toronto
